From: Hector Diaz <hdiazc@live.com>
Subject: [PATCH] kvmfr: add MODULE_DESCRIPTION to silence modpost warning

Linux modpost emits a warning for modules lacking MODULE_DESCRIPTION().
Add one to keep package install logs clean.

--- a/module/kvmfr.c
+++ b/module/kvmfr.c
@@ -650,6 +650,7 @@ module_init(kvmfr_module_init);
 module_exit(kvmfr_module_exit);

 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(pci, kvmfr_pci_ids);
+MODULE_DESCRIPTION("Looking Glass KVMFR shared-memory module for low-latency VFIO/PCI passthrough");
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL v2");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Geoffrey McRae <geoff@hostfission.com>");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Guanzhong Chen <quantum2048@gmail.com>");
